quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  17,11,Insaan sharr (burai) us tarah maangta hai jis tarah khair maangni chahiye. Insaan bada hi jald baaz waqey hua hai
  17,12,"Dekho, humne raat aur din ko do nishaniyan banaya hai. Raat ki nishani ko humne be-noor banaya, aur din ki nishani ko roshan kardiya, taa-ke tum apne Rubb ka fazal talash kar sako aur maah-o-saal ka hisaab maloom kar sako. Isi tarah humne har cheez ko alag alag mumaiyyaz (manifestly distinct) karke rakkha hai"
  17,13,"Har Insaan ka shagun (fate/ augury) humne uske apne galey mein latka rakkha hai, aur qayamat ke roz hum ek nuishta (book/record/scroll) uske liye nikalenge jisey woh khuli kitab ki tarah payega"
  17,14,"Padh apna naam-e-aamal, aaj apna hisaab lagane ke liye tu khud hi kafi hai"
  17,15,"Jo koi raah-e-raast ikhtiyar karey uski raast-rawi uske apne hi liye mufeed hai, aur jo gumraah ho uski gumrahi ka wabal usi par hai. Koi bojh uthane wala dusre ka bojh na uthayega aur hum azaab dene waley nahin hain jabtak ke (logon ko haqq-o-baatil ka farq samjhane ke liye) ek paighambar na bhej dein"
  17,16,"Jab hum kisi basti ko halaak karne ka irada karte hain to uske khush haal logon ko hukum dete hain aur woh usmein nafarmaaniyan karne lagte hain, tab azaab ka faisla us basti par chaspan ho jata hai aur hum usey barbaad karke rakh dete hain"
  17,17,"Dekhlo, kitni hi nasalein (generations) hain jo Nooh ke baad hamare hukum se halaak huyi, tera Rubb apne bandon ke gunaahon se puri tarah bakhabar hai aur sab kuch dekh raha hai"
  17,18,"Jo koi aajila (jaldi) ka khwahish-mand ho, usey yahin hum de detay hain jo kuch bhi jisey dena chahein, phir uske maqsoom mein jahannum likh dete hain jisey woh taapega, malamat zada aur rehmat se mehroon hokar"
  17,19,"Aur jo aakhirat ka khwahish-mand ho aur uske liye sayi (strive) karey jaisi ke uske liye sayi (strive) karni chahiye, aur ho woh momin, to aisey har shaks ki sayi mashkur hogi"
  17,20,"Inko bhi aur unko bhi, dono fareeqon ko hum (duniya mein) saaman-e-zeist diye jaa rahey hain, yeh tere Rubb ka atiya hai, aur tere Rubb ki ata ko rokne wala koi nahin hai"
  17,21,"Magar dekhlo, duniya hi mein humne ek giroh ko dusre par kaisi fazilat de rakkhi hai, aur aakhirat mein uske darje aur bhi zyada honge, aur uski fazilat aur bhi zyada badh chadh kar hogi"
  17,22,"Tu Allah ke saath koi dusra mabood na bana, warna malamat zada aur be yaar o madadgaar baitha reh jayega"